   "source": [
    "### 2.3 Text Length Distribution\n",
    "Fraudulent job postings often differ in length and detail compared to legitimate ones. Let's combine the text fields (`title`, `company_profile`, `description`, `requirements`, and `benefits`) and visualize the distribution of word counts for both classes using a density plot."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "e5f6g7h8",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Combine main text columns into a single string per row\n",
    "text_cols = ['title', 'company_profile', 'description', 'requirements', 'benefits']\n",
    "df['text_combined'] = df[text_cols].fillna('').agg(' '.join, axis=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculate word count for each posting\n",
    "df['word_count'] = df['text_combined'].apply(lambda x: len(str(x).split()))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot the distribution\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))\n",
    "sns.histplot(data=df, x='word_count', hue='fraudulent', bins=100, kde=True, stat='density', common_norm=False, palette={0: 'blue', 1: 'red'})\n",
    "plt.title('Distribution of Word Counts: Legitimate vs. Fraudulent', fontsize=14)\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Word Count', fontsize=12)\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Density', fontsize=12)\n",
    "plt.xlim(0, 1500)  # Truncating long tails for better visualization\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "i9j0k1l2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2.4 Word Clouds by Class\n",
    "To get a sense of the vocabulary used in fake versus real job postings, we will generate word clouds for both categories. This helps identify potential \"trigger words\" that our model might eventually pick up on.\n",
    "\n",
    "*Note: You may need to run `!pip install wordcloud` in your environment if the library is not yet installed.*"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "m3n4o5p6",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from wordcloud import WordCloud, STOPWORDS\n",
    "\n",
    "# Separate text by class\n",
    "text_legit = ' '.join(df[df['fraudulent'] == 0]['text_combined'])\n",
    "text_fraud = ' '.join(df[df['fraudulent'] == 1]['text_combined'])\n",
    "\n",
    "stopwords = set(STOPWORDS)\n",
    "# Add common filler words specific to job postings to filter out noise\n",
    "stopwords.update(['work', 'job', 'will', 'experience', 'company', 'role', 'team', 'position'])\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(16, 8))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Legitimate Word Cloud\n",
    "wc_legit = WordCloud(width=800, height=400, background_color='white', stopwords=stopwords, max_words=150).generate(text_legit)\n",
    "axes.imshow(wc_legit, interpolation='bilinear')\n",
    "axes.set_title('Legitimate Job Postings', fontsize=16)\n",
    "axes.axis('off')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Fraudulent Word Cloud\n",
    "wc_fraud = WordCloud(width=800, height=400, background_color='black', colormap='Reds', stopwords=stopwords, max_words=150).generate(text_fraud)\n",
    "axes.imshow(wc_fraud, interpolation='bilinear')\n",
    "axes.set_title('Fraudulent Job Postings', fontsize=16)\n",
    "axes.axis('off')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  }
